LU said it was running 52 per cent of Tube services today despite the 'pointless' strike, and carried 56 per cent of its usual passenger numbers this morning, which it said was a record for a strike day.

Around 80 per cent of stations were open and services ran on 10 of the 11 lines, said the company.

