Cass Horowitz tweeted a picture of the board with the caption: 'Saw this on the way to work? good to know London still has a sense of humour.'

But many angry Londoners failed to see the funny side.

While the manager of the eatery was quick to apologise for the sign and remove it, many angry Londoners vented their frustration at them online.

The manager tweeted: 'Again, total apology to anyone offended by the board this morning. Was only supposed to be a joke, clearly I got it VERY wrong.'

Despite the apology, dozens of people slammed the joke.

